<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="94" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Young</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-05-26"><hi rend="italic">May 26,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Have again impressed upon Honduras necessity of vigorous action and
                            speedy report upon Renton case. Have received assurance from that
                            Government that they are prosecuting investigation with utmost diligence
                            and vigor, and hope soon to report satisfactory results. Will embark for
                            United States 29th unless otherwise directed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Young.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>